{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The story I wanted to share with you today"},{"time":2000,"text":"is my challenge as an Iranian artist,"},{"time":6000,"text":"as an Iranian woman artist,"},{"time":8000,"text":"as an Iranian woman artist"},{"time":10000,"text":"living in exile."},{"time":13000,"text":"Well, it has its pluses and minuses."},{"time":16000,"text":"On the dark side,"},{"time":18000,"text":"politics doesn't seem to escape people like me."},{"time":21000,"text":"Every Iranian artist, in one form or another,"},{"time":24000,"text":"is political."},{"time":26000,"text":"Politics have defined our lives."},{"time":29000,"text":"If you're living in Iran,"},{"time":31000,"text":"you're facing censorship, harassment,"},{"time":34000,"text":"arrest, torture --"},{"time":36000,"text":"at times, execution."},{"time":39000,"text":"If you're living outside like me,"},{"time":41000,"text":"you're faced with life in exile --"},{"time":43000,"text":"the pain of the longing"},{"time":45000,"text":"and the separation from your loved ones"},{"time":47000,"text":"and your family."},{"time":49000,"text":"Therefore, we don't find"},{"time":51000,"text":"the moral, emotional,"},{"time":53000,"text":"psychological and political space"},{"time":55000,"text":"to distance ourselves from the reality"},{"time":58000,"text":"of social responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"Oddly enough,"},{"time":63000,"text":"an artist such as myself"},{"time":65000,"text":"finds herself also in the position of being the voice,"},{"time":69000,"text":"the speaker of my people,"},{"time":72000,"text":"even if I have, indeed,"},{"time":74000,"text":"no access to my own country."},{"time":77000,"text":"Also, people like myself,"},{"time":80000,"text":"we're fighting two battles on different grounds."},{"time":83000,"text":"We're being critical of the West,"},{"time":85000,"text":"the perception of the West"},{"time":87000,"text":"about our identity --"},{"time":89000,"text":"about the image that is constructed about us,"},{"time":92000,"text":"about our women, about our politics,"},{"time":95000,"text":"about our religion."},{"time":97000,"text":"We are there to take pride"},{"time":99000,"text":"and insist on respect."},{"time":101000,"text":"And at the same time,"},{"time":103000,"text":"we're fighting another battle."},{"time":105000,"text":"That is our regime,"},{"time":107000,"text":"our government --"},{"time":109000,"text":"our atrocious government,"},{"time":111000,"text":"[that] has done every crime"},{"time":113000,"text":"in order to stay in power."},{"time":116000,"text":"Our artists are at risk."},{"time":119000,"text":"We are in a position of danger."},{"time":122000,"text":"We pose a threat"},{"time":124000,"text":"to the order of the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"But ironically,"},{"time":128000,"text":"this situation"},{"time":130000,"text":"has empowered all of us,"},{"time":132000,"text":"because we are considered, as artists,"},{"time":134000,"text":"central to the cultural, political,"},{"time":137000,"text":"social discourse in Iran."},{"time":139000,"text":"We are there to inspire, to provoke,"},{"time":142000,"text":"to mobilize,"},{"time":144000,"text":"to bring hope to our people."},{"time":146000,"text":"We are the reporters of our people,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and are communicators"},{"time":151000,"text":"to the outside world."},{"time":153000,"text":"Art is our weapon."},{"time":156000,"text":"Culture is a form of resistance."},{"time":159000,"text":"I envy sometimes the artists of the West"},{"time":162000,"text":"for their freedom of expression."},{"time":164000,"text":"For the fact that they can distance themselves"},{"time":167000,"text":"from the question of politics."},{"time":169000,"text":"From the fact that they are only serving one audience,"},{"time":171000,"text":"mainly the Western culture."},{"time":174000,"text":"But also, I worry about the West,"},{"time":178000,"text":"because often in this country,"},{"time":180000,"text":"in this Western world that we have,"},{"time":183000,"text":"culture risks being a form of entertainment."},{"time":188000,"text":"Our people depend on our artists,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and culture is beyond communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"My journey as an artist"},{"time":197000,"text":"started from a very, very personal place."},{"time":200000,"text":"I did not start"},{"time":202000,"text":"to make social commentary"},{"time":204000,"text":"about my country."},{"time":206000,"text":"The first one that you see in front of you"},{"time":209000,"text":"is actually when I first returned to Iran"},{"time":211000,"text":"after being separated for a good 12 years."},{"time":214000,"text":"It was after the Islamic Revolution"},{"time":216000,"text":"of 1979."},{"time":219000,"text":"While I was absent from Iran,"},{"time":222000,"text":"the Islamic Revolution had descended on Iran"},{"time":225000,"text":"and had entirely transformed the country"},{"time":227000,"text":"from Persian to the Islamic culture."},{"time":230000,"text":"I came mainly to be reunited with my family"},{"time":233000,"text":"and to reconnect in a way"},{"time":235000,"text":"that I found my place in the society."},{"time":237000,"text":"But instead, I found a country"},{"time":239000,"text":"that was totally ideological"},{"time":241000,"text":"and that I didn't recognize anymore."},{"time":244000,"text":"More so, I became very interested,"},{"time":246000,"text":"as I was facing"},{"time":248000,"text":"my own personal dilemmas and questions,"},{"time":250000,"text":"I became immersed in the study"},{"time":252000,"text":"of the Islamic Revolution --"},{"time":254000,"text":"how, indeed,"},{"time":256000,"text":"it had incredibly transformed"},{"time":258000,"text":"the lives of Iranian women."},{"time":260000,"text":"I found the subject of Iranian women"},{"time":262000,"text":"immensely interesting,"},{"time":264000,"text":"in the way the women of Iran, historically,"},{"time":267000,"text":"seemed to embody the political transformation."},{"time":270000,"text":"So in a way, by studying a woman,"},{"time":273000,"text":"you can read the structure and the ideology of the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"So I made a group of work"},{"time":279000,"text":"that at once faced my own personal questions in life,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and yet it brought my work into a larger discourse --"},{"time":286000,"text":"the subject of martyrdom,"},{"time":288000,"text":"the question of those who willingly stand in that intersection"},{"time":292000,"text":"of love of God, faith,"},{"time":296000,"text":"but violence and crime and cruelty."},{"time":299000,"text":"For me, this became incredibly important."},{"time":302000,"text":"And yet, I had an unusual position toward this."},{"time":305000,"text":"I was an outsider"},{"time":307000,"text":"who had come back to Iran to find my place,"},{"time":310000,"text":"but I was not in a position"},{"time":312000,"text":"to be critical of the government"},{"time":315000,"text":"or the ideology of the Islamic Revolution."},{"time":318000,"text":"This changed slowly"},{"time":320000,"text":"as I found my voice"},{"time":322000,"text":"and I discovered things"},{"time":324000,"text":"that I didn't know I would discover."},{"time":326000,"text":"So my art became slightly more critical."},{"time":329000,"text":"My knife became a little sharper."},{"time":331000,"text":"And I fell into a life in exile."},{"time":335000,"text":"I am a nomadic artist."},{"time":337000,"text":"I work in Morocco, in Turkey, in Mexico."},{"time":340000,"text":"I go everywhere to make believe it's Iran."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"Now I am making films."},{"time":345000,"text":"Last year, I finished a film"},{"time":347000,"text":"called \"Women Without Men.\""},{"time":349000,"text":"\"Women Without Men\" returns to history,"},{"time":351000,"text":"but another part of our Iranian history."},{"time":354000,"text":"It goes to 1953"},{"time":356000,"text":"when American CIA exercised a coup"},{"time":359000,"text":"and removed a democratically elected leader,"},{"time":361000,"text":"Dr. Mossadegh."},{"time":363000,"text":"The book is written by an Iranian woman,"},{"time":365000,"text":"Shahrnush Parsipur."},{"time":367000,"text":"It's a magical realist novel."},{"time":369000,"text":"This book is banned,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and she spent five years in prison."},{"time":373000,"text":"My obsession with this book,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and the reason I made this into a film,"},{"time":377000,"text":"is because it at once was addressing"},{"time":379000,"text":"the question of being a female --"},{"time":381000,"text":"traditionally, historically in Iran --"},{"time":384000,"text":"and the question of four women"},{"time":386000,"text":"who are all looking for an idea"},{"time":388000,"text":"of change, freedom and democracy --"},{"time":391000,"text":"while the country of Iran, equally, as if another character,"},{"time":394000,"text":"also struggled for an idea"},{"time":396000,"text":"of freedom and democracy"},{"time":398000,"text":"and independence from the foreign interventions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"I made this film"},{"time":403000,"text":"because I felt it's important"},{"time":405000,"text":"for it to speak to the Westerners"},{"time":407000,"text":"about our history as a country."},{"time":410000,"text":"That all of you seem to remember Iran"},{"time":412000,"text":"after the Islamic Revolution."},{"time":414000,"text":"That Iran was once a secular society,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and we had democracy,"},{"time":419000,"text":"and this democracy was stolen from us"},{"time":421000,"text":"by the American government,"},{"time":423000,"text":"by the British government."},{"time":425000,"text":"This film also speaks to the Iranian people"},{"time":428000,"text":"in asking them to return to their history"},{"time":430000,"text":"and look at themselves before they were so Islamicized --"},{"time":434000,"text":"in the way we looked, in the way we played music,"},{"time":437000,"text":"in the way we had intellectual life."},{"time":441000,"text":"And most of all,"},{"time":443000,"text":"in the way that we fought for democracy."},{"time":446000,"text":"These are some of the shots actually from my film."},{"time":449000,"text":"These are some of the images of the coup."},{"time":451000,"text":"And we made this film in Casablanca,"},{"time":454000,"text":"recreating all the shots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"This film tried to find a balance"},{"time":459000,"text":"between telling a political story,"},{"time":461000,"text":"but also a feminine story."},{"time":463000,"text":"Being a visual artist, indeed,"},{"time":465000,"text":"I am foremost interested to make art --"},{"time":468000,"text":"to make art that transcends"},{"time":470000,"text":"politics, religion,"},{"time":472000,"text":"the question of feminism,"},{"time":475000,"text":"and become an important, timeless,"},{"time":477000,"text":"universal work of art."},{"time":479000,"text":"The challenge I have"},{"time":481000,"text":"is how to do that."},{"time":483000,"text":"How to tell a political story but an allegorical story."},{"time":486000,"text":"How to move you with your emotions,"},{"time":488000,"text":"but also make your mind work."},{"time":490000,"text":"These are some of the images"},{"time":492000,"text":"and the characters of the film."},{"time":505000,"text":"Now comes the green movement --"},{"time":507000,"text":"the summer of 2009,"},{"time":509000,"text":"as my film is released --"},{"time":511000,"text":"the uprising begins in the streets of Tehran."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"What is unbelievably ironic"},{"time":517000,"text":"is the period that we tried to depict in the film,"},{"time":520000,"text":"the cry for democracy"},{"time":522000,"text":"and social justice,"},{"time":524000,"text":"repeats itself now"},{"time":526000,"text":"again in Tehran."},{"time":528000,"text":"The green movement"},{"time":530000,"text":"significantly inspired the world."},{"time":532000,"text":"It brought a lot of attention to all those Iranians"},{"time":535000,"text":"who stand for basic human rights"},{"time":537000,"text":"and struggle for democracy."},{"time":539000,"text":"What was most significant for me"},{"time":541000,"text":"was, once again,"},{"time":543000,"text":"the presence of the women."},{"time":545000,"text":"They're absolutely inspirational for me."},{"time":547000,"text":"If in the Islamic Revolution,"},{"time":549000,"text":"the images of the woman portrayed"},{"time":551000,"text":"were submissive"},{"time":553000,"text":"and didn't have a voice,"},{"time":555000,"text":"now we saw a new idea of feminism"},{"time":557000,"text":"in the streets of Tehran --"},{"time":560000,"text":"women who were educated,"},{"time":562000,"text":"forward thinking, non-traditional,"},{"time":564000,"text":"sexually open, fearless"},{"time":567000,"text":"and seriously feminist."},{"time":570000,"text":"These women and those young men"},{"time":573000,"text":"united Iranians"},{"time":575000,"text":"across the world, inside and outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"I then discovered"},{"time":580000,"text":"why I take so much inspiration"},{"time":582000,"text":"from Iranian women."},{"time":584000,"text":"That, under all circumstances,"},{"time":586000,"text":"they have pushed the boundary."},{"time":588000,"text":"They have confronted the authority."},{"time":590000,"text":"They have broken every rule"},{"time":592000,"text":"in the smallest and the biggest way."},{"time":594000,"text":"And once again, they proved themselves."},{"time":596000,"text":"I stand here to say"},{"time":598000,"text":"that Iranian women have found a new voice,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and their voice is giving me my voice."},{"time":604000,"text":"And it's a great honor"},{"time":606000,"text":"to be an Iranian woman and an Iranian artist,"},{"time":609000,"text":"even if I have to operate in the West only for now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}